.\" PDF Text Extraction Analysis Tool Manual Page
.TH pdftextanalysis 1 "10 February 2026"
.SH NAME
pdftextanalysis \- PDF text extraction analysis tool
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B pdftextanalysis
[options]
.I PDF-file
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B pdftextanalysis
analyzes a PDF file to determine the CID to Unicode mapping completeness for each page.
It classifies pages into five categories based on character-level Unicode mapping state:
.PP
.B IMAGE
\- No text objects exist (image-based PDF)
.PP
.B UNICODE_ALL_MATCH
\- All characters have valid Unicode mappings and sufficient character count (> 10 chars)
.PP
.B UNICODE_ALL_MATCH_BUT_LESS_CHARS
\- All characters have valid Unicode mappings but character count is low (<= 10 chars)
.br
This typically indicates pages with only page numbers, headers, or footers
.PP
.B UNICODE_NONE_MATCH
\- No characters have valid Unicode mappings
.PP
.B UNICODE_PARTIAL_MATCH
\- Some but not all characters have valid Unicode mappings
.PP
The tool outputs results in JSON format to stdout, suitable for automated processing
and integration with other tools.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-v
Print version info.
.TP
.B \-h
Print usage information.
.TP
.B \-help
Print usage information.
.TP
.B \-\-help
Print usage information.
.SH OUTPUT FORMAT
The tool outputs JSON to stdout with the following structure.
.PP
.B Successful analysis:
.PP
.nf
{
  "status": "OK",
  "pages": [
    {"page": 1, "type": "UNICODE_ALL_MATCH"},
    {"page": 2, "type": "UNICODE_PARTIAL_MATCH"},
    {"page": 3, "type": "UNICODE_NONE_MATCH"},
    {"page": 4, "type": "IMAGE"}
  ]
}
.fi
.PP
.B Document-level failure:
.PP
.nf
{
  "status": "ERROR",
  "error": "PDF_OPEN_FAILED"
}
.fi
.PP
.B Success response fields:
.TP
.B status
Always "OK" on successful analysis
.TP
.B pages
Array of page analysis results
.PP
Each page entry contains:
.TP
.B page
The page number (1-indexed)
.TP
.B type
The classification: "IMAGE", "UNICODE_ALL_MATCH", "UNICODE_ALL_MATCH_BUT_LESS_CHARS",
"UNICODE_NONE_MATCH", or "UNICODE_PARTIAL_MATCH"
.PP
.B Error response fields:
.TP
.B status
Always "ERROR" on document-level failure
.TP
.B error
Error reason code (see ERROR CODES section)
.SH CLASSIFICATION LOGIC
The tool uses deterministic logic based on CID to Unicode mapping completeness:
.PP
.B Step 1: Count drawChar operations
.PP
Each character drawing operation is tracked to determine if text objects exist.
.PP
.B Step 2: Count valid Unicode mappings
.PP
For each character, check if a valid Unicode mapping exists. A mapping is considered
invalid if:
.PP
   - The Unicode length is 0 (no mapping provided)
.PP
   - The Unicode pointer is null
.PP
   - The Unicode value is U+FFFD (replacement character, indicating mapping failure)
.PP
.B Step 3: Classify based on mapping completeness and character count
.PP
The minimum character threshold is 10 characters.
.PP
   - If drawCharCount == 0 → 
.B IMAGE
.PP
   - If unicodeMappedCount == drawCharCount AND drawCharCount > 10 →
.B UNICODE_ALL_MATCH
.PP
   - If unicodeMappedCount == drawCharCount AND drawCharCount <= 10 →
.B UNICODE_ALL_MATCH_BUT_LESS_CHARS
.PP
   - If unicodeMappedCount == 0 →
.B UNICODE_NONE_MATCH
.PP
   - Otherwise →
.B UNICODE_PARTIAL_MATCH
.SH EXAMPLES
Analyze a PDF file:
.PP
.nf
pdftextanalysis document.pdf
.fi
.PP
Use with Python for automated processing with error handling:
.PP
.nf
import subprocess, json

result = subprocess.run(['pdftextanalysis', 'doc.pdf'],
                       capture_output=True, text=True)
data = json.loads(result.stdout)

if data['status'] == 'ERROR':
    print(f"Document-level error: {data['error']}")
    if data['error'] == 'PDF_OPEN_FAILED':
        print("File may be corrupted or invalid")
    elif data['error'] == 'PDF_PERMISSION_DENIED':
        print("File is DRM-protected")
else:
    # Process page-level results
    for page in data['pages']:
        print(f"Page {page['page']}: {page['type']}")
.fi
.PP
Example decision logic based on page classification:
.PP
.nf
if page_type in ["IMAGE", "UNICODE_ALL_MATCH_BUT_LESS_CHARS"]:
    # Use OCR (no text or only page numbers/headers)
elif page_type == "UNICODE_ALL_MATCH":
    # Direct text extraction reliable
elif page_type in ["UNICODE_NONE_MATCH", "UNICODE_PARTIAL_MATCH"]:
    # Consider OCR or font-specific extraction
.fi
.SH ERROR CODES
When status is "ERROR", the error field contains one of the following codes:
.TP
.B PDF_OPEN_FAILED
The PDF file could not be opened or parsed. This indicates file corruption,
invalid PDF format, or inaccessible file.
.TP
.B PDF_PERMISSION_DENIED
The PDF file is protected by DRM or permissions that prevent text extraction.
This check is only performed if ENFORCE_PERMISSIONS was enabled at build time.
.PP
.B Note on rendering errors:
Poppler is compiled without exception handling. If a fatal rendering error occurs
during page processing (e.g., severely corrupted content), the program will
terminate abnormally rather than returning a structured error response.
.PP
These are document-level failures detected before rendering.
They are NOT inferred from page statistics.
.SH EXIT CODES
The pdftextanalysis utility exits with one of the following values:
.TP
.B 0
Successful completion (status: "OK").
.TP
.B 1
Failed to open the PDF file (error: "PDF_OPEN_FAILED").
.TP
.B 3
Permission denied (error: "PDF_PERMISSION_DENIED").
.TP
.B 99
Invalid command line arguments.
.PP
If a fatal rendering error occurs during page processing, the program will
terminate abnormally with a non-zero exit code determined by Poppler.
.SH AUTHOR
This tool was developed as an extension to the Poppler PDF rendering library.
